Discussion: Creating an Ancestor 

This sequence of production-from gathering cot­ton to adding the last inlay-is seemingly straight­forward; but this is no simple object. The materials combine to create a remarkable "being" -a phys­ical representation of an ancestor. The cotton weave becomes a metaphor for his skin; the stone weight, his viscera; the Jianas, the bones and sinews of his arms and legs; the wood,his backbone. The human 
